{
  "doc_id": "2980",
  "text": "Vaccines are one of the world's most powerful public health interventions. Many of the currently licensed human vaccines are believed to confer protection through the induction of antigen-specific antibodies [CITATION_1] . These include vaccines against a range of viral pathogens such as hepatitis [CITATION_2] , human papilloma virus [CITATION_3] , polio [CITATION_4] , influenza [CITATION_5] and yellow fever [CITATION_6] , and the bacterial pathogens including pneumococcus [CITATION_7] and pertussis [CITATION_8] .",
